Package: multiclosure
Type: Package
Title: Multivariate CLOSURE for Forensic Reconstruction of Bounded-Integer Datasets
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Ian", "Hussey", email = "ian.hussey@example.org", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Extends CLOSURE (Jung, unsum package) to the multivariate case.
    Given reported summary statistics for Likert-style data (sample size,
    per-item means and SDs, correlation matrix, optionally Cronbach's alpha),
    enumerate or sample integer datasets compatible with those summaries on
    the stated bounded scale. Intended for forensic use: detect papers whose
    reported summaries are infeasible, internally inconsistent, or whose
    claimed inferences cannot be reproduced on any compatible reconstruction.
    Pipeline runs cheap impossibility certificates first (GRIM/GRIMMER,
    Bhatia-Davis, Cronbach alpha consistency, Frechet-Hoeffding bounds),
    then per-item CLOSURE enumeration, a beta-binomial population-skew
    plausibility filter, NORTA-based joint reconstruction via GenOrd, and
    a summary-verification step. A mixed-integer fallback for
    NORTA-infeasible cases is planned for v2.
